    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Market Research Regarding the Introduction of a New Hair Colour Brand for Salons</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Romeo Antony S.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Market Research Regarding<br />New Hair Colour Brand</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5609</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A MARKET RESEARCH REGARDING THE INTRODUCTION OF A NEW HAIR COLOUR BRAND FOR SALONS
The project topic entitled, ” A MARKET RESEARCH REGARDING THE INTRODUCTION OF A NEW HAIR COLOUR BRAND FOR SALONS “ is a study conducted to analyse the various demands available in salons for our new hair colour brand to be introduced. The area of study is limited to the areas in and around Chennai.
Through examining the impact of a new hair colour brand on the market and brand
performance measures, we contribute to the growing body of knowledge concerning new
brand behaviour. Using 4 weeks worth of panel data, we evaluated the impact of a new
hair colour product launch in the salons in and around Chennai, looking at how it may perform in terms of gaining buyers and how well the product will move in the market.
During our period of survey, we coverd all 3 major type of salons namely- Unisex, Male and Female type. This helped us in understanding the momentum within which the hair colour products are being sold. Hair colouring has become a major trend among the people in Chennai and is a fast moving business , as said by a major salon in the city. There is more scope for our product, if we set up a tie with the most outstanding salons in the city and so my project study is restricted only to the salons .
We also examined how the competitor parameters of the market were affected by the new entry of our product that will be launched. Our findings suggest that new brands look just like established brands within the short term. Finally, it appears that there are no obvious effects on the normal patterns of competition.</td></tr>
